# Agentic Video Generation (Cursor rule)

This repo lets **any coding agent** turn a topic into a real MP4 with the agent
making every decision. No Google Gemini / Ollama key required for the default
`agent` backend (signal-level verification only).

## Commands
```bash
npm run agentic -- --topic "..." --title "..." --backend agent --orientation landscape --images
npm run agentic:batch          # generate + verify 3 videos
```

## Import
```ts
import { runAgenticPipeline, renderAgenticSlideshow } from './src/agentic/orchestrate.js';
```

## MCP tools (server: `npx tsx src/mcp-server.ts`)
`agentic_run` (one-shot) or granular `agentic_plan` / `agentic_acquire` /
`agentic_verify_all` / `agentic_list_pending` / `agentic_approve` /
`agentic_reject` / `agentic_gate`.

## Rules
- NodeNext: relative imports MUST use `.js` (e.g. `from './plan.js'`).
- Legacy `npm run generate` workflow is UNCHANGED — keep changes additive under
  `src/agentic/`.
- `agentic-pipeline/workspaces/` is git-ignored (runtime artifacts).
- Verify with `npm run typecheck` + `npm run test:unit`.
- Do NOT commit/push without explicit user approval.
